# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 15:57:23
<overview>
<p>The Dragau is a 2,500-ton Aerodyne assault interceptor originally developed by the Word of Blake as a testbed for automated drone control systems. Based on an existing DropShip hull, the design was conceived to evaluate whether unmanned combat vessels could match or exceed the performance of crewed interceptors in high-intensity naval engagements. The results exceeded expectations, producing a weapons platform of extraordinary lethality.</p><p>Without a crew to protect, the Dragau can maintain acceleration rates and execute maneuvers that would kill human occupants, giving it a decisive edge in close-quarters combat. The combination of heavy armor, devastating forward firepower, and extreme agility made the Dragau one of the most feared DropShip-scale combatants of its era, and its successors have continued to serve in naval forces well into the thirty-second century.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The original Dragau concentrates overwhelming firepower in its nose arc, mounting two heavy Gauss rifles and six heavy PPCs as its primary armament. Each wing carries two LRM-15 racks with Artemis IV fire control, two ER PPCs, and four large variable-speed pulse lasers. The aft arc mounts two additional large variable-speed pulse lasers and three anti-missile systems to discourage pursuit. Four nose-mounted anti-missile systems supplement the forward defenses. One hundred and twenty double heat sinks manage the immense thermal output.</p><p>Protected by sixty-six tons of heavy ferro-aluminum armor weighing as much as a heavy BattleMech, the Dragau can absorb punishment that would cripple conventional DropShips. The CASPAR II Advanced Smart Robotic Control System serves as the vessel's brain, coordinating attacks through command ships and providing an inherent ECM effect that further enhances survivability. Safe thrust of nine Gs makes the Dragau extraordinarily agile for a vessel of its tonnage, enabling maneuvers impossible for crewed interceptors.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The standard Dragau II Assault Interceptor is the manned production variant developed after the fall of the Word of Blake. Based on the original Caspar II drone interceptor hull, the Dragau II restores a conventional crew complement while retaining the aggressive performance characteristics of its predecessor. The manned version necessarily sacrifices some of the extreme acceleration tolerances that made the drone variant so lethal, but compensates with improved tactical flexibility and the ability to exercise independent judgment during complex fleet engagements. Produced for the Republic of the Sphere's nascent navy, the Dragau II serves as a fast interceptor capable of running down fleeing vessels or screening larger capital assets.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The original Dragau entered service in 3065 as the Word of Blake's primary evaluation platform for their advanced drone control technology. Live-fire testing during the assault on Mars demonstrated the concept's viability in devastating fashion, as Dragau drones destroyed the majority of the attacking force's aerospace and WarShip support. The success of these initial engagements led to full-scale production and deployment across Blakist-controlled space.</p><p>During the final battle for Terra, a damaged Dragau destroyed a major Coalition WarShip, further cementing the design's fearsome reputation. Following the defeat of the Word of Blake, surviving Dragau hulls and their underlying technology were studied extensively. The Republic of the Sphere subsequently commissioned a crewed successor design, the Dragau II, which entered production in 3085. This variant retained the original's devastating weapons configuration while replacing the drone control system with conventional crew facilities. Further refinements in 3097 incorporated advanced networking systems to improve coordination within larger fleet formations.</p>
</history>

